quran[30]{c,v,t}:
  21,83,"And Job, when he cried to his Lord, saying, \"Lo! Adversity has touched me, but you are the most Merciful of the merciful ones"
  21,84,"And We answered him, and removed from him the distress that was upon him; and We restored to him his people, and doubled their number as a mercy from Us, and as a remembrance to those who serve Us"
  21,85,"And (remember) Ishmael, and Idris (Enoch?), and Zul-Kifl (Ezekiel?), all men of constancy and patient"
  21,86,"And We admitted them into Our Mercy; verily, they were among the righteous"
  21,87,"And remember Zun-nun (the man of the Whale, Jonah), when he went away in wrath and thought that We had no power over him; but he cried out in the darkness, \"There is no God but Thou, celebrated be Thy praise! Verily, I was of the wrong"
  21,88,"And We answered him, and saved him from the distress. Thus do We deliver those who have faith"
  21,89,"And (remember) Zachariah, when he cried unto his Lord, \"O Lord! Leave me not without off-spring, though you are the best of inheritors"
  21,90,"And We answered him, and bestowed upon him Yahya (John); and We made his wife right for him (cured her barrenness). Verily, they used to vie with one another in good works, and they called unto Us with longing and awe, and were humble (or submissive) befo"
  21,91,"And (remember) her who guarded her chastity, and We breathed into her of Our Spirit, and We made her and her son a sign unto the worlds (or all peoples, or all creatures)"
  21,92,"Verily, this your religion (or brotherhood) is a single religion (brotherhood); and I am your Lord, so serve Me"
  21,93,"But they cut up their affairs (religion, politics etc. into fragments) amongst themselves, yet they all shall return unto Us"
  21,94,"And he who acts right and he who is a believer (or has faith), there is no denial of his efforts, for, verily, We record it for him"
  21,95,There is a ban upon any community which We have destroyed that they shall not return
  21,96,"Until Yagug and Magug (Gog and Magog, Lawless tribes or Lawlessness itself) are let loose (through every barrier), and they hasten out of every mound (rock, nook and cranny)"
  21,97,"And the True Promise draws nigh, and lo! They are staring, wide-eyed are those who disbelieve, saying, \"O, woe is us! We were heedless of this, aye, we were wrong-doers"
  21,98,"Verily, ye, and what you serve beside Allah, shall be the fuel of hell. Thereto shall you go down"
  21,99,"Had these been gods, they would not have come hither, but all shall dwell therein"
  21,100,"For them therein is groaning, and they shall not be heard"
  21,101,"Verily, those for whom the Good from Us has gone before, they will be removed far there from"
  21,102,"They shall not hear the slightest sound of Hell, and they will dwell in what their souls desire"
  21,103,"The Great Terror shall not grieve them; but the angels shall greet them, saying, \"This is your day, the one which you were promised"
  21,104,"The Day when We will roll up the heavens as a recorder rolls up the scroll. As We produced it at its first creation, We shall repeat it - a promise binding upon Us; verily, We shall do it"
  21,105,"And already have We written in the Psalms after the Reminder (the Message of Moses) that \"My righteous servants shall inherit the earth"
  21,106,"Verily, in this is a plain statement for a people who serve Me"
  21,107,"We have sent you not, but as a mercy to the worlds"
  21,108,"Say, \"I am only inspired that your God is one God; will ye, then, surrender unto Him (become Muslims)"
  21,109,"But if they turn their backs, then say, \"I have proclaimed the message to you all alike, though I know not if what you are promised be near or far"
  21,110,"Verily, He knows what is spoken openly, and that which you hide"
  21,111,"I know not but that this may be a trial for you, and provision for a season"
  21,112,"Say, \"O My Lord! Judge you with truth! Our Lord is the Beneficent Whose aid is to be sought against the blasphemies you utter"